## Context

- All 5 phases implemented and running in `pipelines/pancancer-ferroptosis-atlas/`
- Phase 1: 1186 lines, 20 genes, 30 cancer types ranked. Top: Lymphoid, Bone, Myeloid, PNS
- Phase 2: 48 NRF2-active lines. FSP1/NRF2 independence confirmed. No FDR-significant results (power-limited)
- Phase 3: TCGA NRF2-WT fractions integrated, FSP1 2x weighted. PRISM: 0 ferroptosis compounds in 24Q2. Expression signature for 33 lineages
- Phase 4: NSCLC KEAP1-mut reference from 11 lines. Top analogs: Bowel, Biliary, Breast. 8 divergent types identified
- Phase 5 (Task #761): FSP1/AIFM2 expression layer + defense profile classification
  - 1699 lines with expression, 1112 with expression+dependency
  - 4 defense profiles: GPX4-dependent (292), FSP1-dependent (292), dual-high (264), dual-low (264)
  - Top dual-high: Liver 67%, Eye 60%, Cervix 56%, Biliary Tract 53%, Pancreas 48%
  - KEAP1→FSP1 upregulation confirmed in Lung (d=0.91, p=0.005). Other types lack KEAP1-mut sample size.
  - KEAP1 boxplot skipped (only Lung has ≥3 KEAP1-mut lines)
- Task #127: Fixed PRISM substring match bug. Added word boundary regex. Added auranofin to compound list.
- Task #302: Added Translational Confidence addendum (Section 8) to report.md.
